g it or have ended diplomatic ties with the island.\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.8739429997529315, \"rank\": 0.08934381514965271, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainland_China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather than see it as its own country, the People's Republic of China (PRC) government classes it as a breakaway province and believes it should come under Beijing's rule.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 2001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1901, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9999979498382442, \"rank\": 2.0462336900823765e-06, \"text\": \"PRC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"score\": 0.999999904691781, \"rank\": 9.530632778522671e-08, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an effort to ease political tensions, it was agreed with the IOC in 1981 that Taiwan could compete at international events under the name Chinese Taipei.\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2066, \"end\": 2069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2907404267404565e-20, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2083, \"end\": 2089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_area_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"score\": 0.6074561462003818, \"rank\": 0.6460924260461889, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_area_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_area_of_the_Republic_of_China\"}, {\"begin\": 2151, \"end\": 2157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9999723072202051, \"rank\": 2.6826268408771524e-05, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_Republic_of_China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So for decades, Taiwanese athletes have competed as representatives of Chinese Taipei rather than Taiwan -\\u00a0a rule that the International Olympic Committee (IOC) strictly enforces.\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"score\": 0.9999126102868184, \"rank\": 8.731136992357742e-05, \"text\": \"Taiwanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9999723072202051, \"rank\": 2.6826268408771524e-05, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_the_Republic_of_China\"}, {\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_area_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"score\": 0.6074561462003818, \"rank\": 0.6460924260461889, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_area_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Free_area_of_the_Republic_of_China\"}, {\